      "question": "For an Arithmetic Progression (AP) defined by $a_n = 5n - 3$, the common difference $d$ is:",
      "answer": "(B)",
      "solution": {
        "steps": [
          "Find the first term $a_1$ by substituting $n = 1$ into the formula: $a_1 = 5(1) - 3 = 2$.",
          "Find the second term $a_2$ by substituting $n = 2$ into the formula: $a_2 = 5(2) - 3 = 7$.",
          "Calculate the common difference $d$ using the formula $d = a_2 - a_1$.",
          "Substitute the values: $d = 7 - 2 = 5$."
        ],
        "derivation": "$a_n = 5n - 3 \\\\ a_1 = 5(1) - 3 = 2 \\\\ a_2 = 5(2) - 3 = 7 \\\\ d = a_2 - a_1 = 7 - 2 = 5$"
